        "solution": "<p style=\"orphans:2;widows:2\"> <span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">The great Buddhist philosopher</span></span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><b>Nagarjuna</b></span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">was described by Chinese traveller Hiuen Tsang as \"one of the four lights of the world.\" Nagarjuna is regarded as the founder of the Madhyamaka school of Mahayana Buddhism. Due to his profound logical and philosophical contributions, he is also called the</span></span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><b>Indian Einstein</b></span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>"
